ten in kana / kanji just for the fun of it.<br>
<br>
One of the words I went through was 'denwa' (phone), and the resulting symbols looked like kanji to me (as in, complicated). The program didn't offer any &quot;alternate&quot; writing methods for the word, so I got to thinking if japanese -reading people would understand 'denwa' written in katakana / hiragana?<br>
<br>
You know, by writing de-n-wa? Would they understand that I meant 'phone', or would they give me a prompt spanking for such blatant misuse of the language? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->       <br>
